This summary provides a brief description of the following elements:



  *  The accidental release provision and emergency response policies;

  *  The stationary sources and regulated substances handled;

  *  The general accidental release prevention program and chemical-specific prevention steps;

  *  The five-year accident history;

  *  The emergency response program, and

  *  Planned changes to improve safety.



ACCIDENTAL RELEASE PROVISION AND EMERGENCY RESPONSE



     The Chemours Belle Plant is committed to operating and maintaining all processes in a safe and responsible

manner by adhering to Corporate Policies that embody the following philosophies:



  *  All safety and environmental incidents are preventable;

  *  The goal for safety and environmental incidents is zero;

  *  All employees and contractors are responsible for their safety.



    The Chemours Belle Plant adheres to Corporate Policies embodied in numerous Environmental, Health and Safety Standards (EHS) and Engineering Standards.  The policies are implemented through the Chemours Belle Plant Environmental, Health and Safety manuals.  These manuals are available to all employees.  Included in these standards are the requirements on Process Safety Management (PSM), under OSHA.  The site also maintains an active PSM committee and routinely conducts first party compliance audits.



    Another integral part of the program on accidental release prevention and emergency response is embodied in the guidelines under Responsible Care, a program developed by the American Chemistry Council.   The site actively participates in this program and has established standing meetings and reviews to ensure continued adherence to the principles and practices set forth under Responsible Care.



